# Service & Landing Page Button Styles

Use these exact patterns for primary and secondary buttons so they match the blog article pages and service [slug] pages.

## On light background

- **Primary (solid):**  
  `class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl h-12 px-8 text-base font-semibold bg-primary !text-white hover:bg-primary/90 shadow-lg transition-all"`  
  Use `!text-white` (not `text-primary-foreground`) so the label stays white.

- **Secondary (outline):**  
  `class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl h-12 px-8 text-base font-semibold border-2 border-primary !text-[#004080] bg-transparent hover:bg-primary/10 transition-all"`  
  Use `!text-[#004080]` for the blue label so it doesn’t inherit a wrong color.

## On primary (dark) background (e.g. CTA band)

- **Primary CTA (white button):**  
  `class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl h-12 px-8 text-base font-semibold bg-white hover:bg-white/90 shadow-lg transition"`  
  Plus `style="color: #004080;"` so the text is brand blue.

- **Secondary (white outline):**  
  `class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl h-12 px-8 text-base font-semibold border-2 border-white text-white hover:bg-white/20 transition"`  
  Use `hover:bg-white/20` (not `hover:bg-white/10`) to match blog CTAs.

## Consistency

- Use `rounded-xl` and `h-12 px-8` for these buttons.
- Do not use `text-primary` or `text-primary-foreground` for button text; use `!text-white` or `!text-[#004080]` or `style="color: #004080;"` as above.
